iable is expected to be an integer type which can be incremented\\r\\natomically.  Expected to be used where certain object's \\\"freshness\\\" is\\r\\nvital, e.g. when invalidating a cache.\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1803\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1803/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1803/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1803/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1803\",\"id\":292549691,\"number\":1803,\"title\":\"Fix bug: Vector#angle_with with linearly dependent vectors\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"Saugardas\",\"id\":9009981,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/9009981?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Saugardas\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/Saugardas\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Saugardas/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Saugardas/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Saugardas/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Saugardas/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Saugardas/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Saugardas/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Saugardas/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Saugardas/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Saugardas/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":2,\"created_at\":\"2018-01-29T20:30:51Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2018-02-23T03:07:44Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/pulls/1803\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1803\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1803.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1803.patch\"},\"body\":\"Vector#angle_with sometimes raises error with linearly dependent vectors:\\r\\n\\r\\n```\\r\\nrequire 'matrix'\\r\\nVector[6, 6].angle_with(Vector[7, 7]) # => Math::DomainError (Numerical argument is out of domain - \\\"acos\\\")\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is due to rounding errors:\\r\\n\\r\\n```\\r\\nprod = magnitude * v.magnitude # =>  8.48528137423857 * 9.899494936611665 -> 83.99999999999999\\r\\nMath.acos(inner_product(v) / prod) # => Math.acos(84 / 83.99) -> Math.acos(1.0000000000000002)\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nThis patch explicitly return zero/Math::PI for linearly dependent vectors.\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1802\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1802/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1802/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1802/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1802\",\"id\":292288323,\"number\":1802,\"title\":\"[Feature #4824]ruby.c: implement Kernel#executed?\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"naofumi-fujii\",\"id\":15604014,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/15604014?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/naofumi-fujii\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/naofumi-fujii\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/naofumi-fujii/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/naofumi-fujii/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/naofumi-fujii/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/naofumi-fujii/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/naofumi-fujii/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/naofumi-fujii/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/naofumi-fujii/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/naofumi-fujii/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/naofumi-fujii/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2018-01-29T05:28:14Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2018-02-23T03:07:43Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/pulls/1802\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1802\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1802.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1802.patch\"},\"body\":\"* ruby.c (f_executed_p): returns true when file is executed directly.\\r\\nreturns false when file is required file. [Feature #4824]\\r\\n\\r\\nrefs\\r\\n--\\r\\nFeature #4824: Provide method Kernel#executed? - Ruby trunk - Ruby Issue Tracking System https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/4824\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1798\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1798/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1798/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1798/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1798\",\"id\":291762964,\"number\":1798,\"title\":\"Speed up full scan completion in IRB\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"dgutov\",\"id\":271877,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/271877?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/dgutov\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/dgutov\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/dgutov/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/dg