",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/yuki24/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/yuki24/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/yuki24/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/yuki24/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/yuki24/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/yuki24/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false}],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":12,\"created_at\":\"2018-01-26T00:27:52Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2018-02-23T03:07:43Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/pulls/1798\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1798\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1798.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1798.patch\"},\"body\":\"This greatly improves completion performance in the full scan case (when IRB doesn't know the type of the call target).\\r\\n\\r\\nIt's particularly noticeable in large projects. Here's how to emulate one:\\r\\n\\r\\n```rb\\r\\nN = 40000\\r\\n\\r\\n# Save the references to avoid GC.\\r\\nmodules = (1..N).map do |i|\\r\\n  Module.new do\\r\\n    module_eval <<-DEF\\r\\n      def foo#{i}\\r\\n      end\\r\\nDEF\\r\\n  end\\r\\nend; nil\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nIn such an environment, this branch brings completion time from ~1 second to almost instantaneous. This code (or close enough) has already been added to Pry and released in version 0.11.0. Here's the relevant report there: https://github.com/pry/pry/issues/1540\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1790\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1790/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1790/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1790/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1790\",\"id\":289191092,\"number\":1790,\"title\":\"Removing duplicated assertions on test_array.rb - MINUS method\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"esparta\",\"id\":1037088,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/1037088?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/esparta\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2018-01-17T09:12:34Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2018-02-23T03:07:43Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/pulls/1790\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1790\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1790.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1790.patch\"},\"body\":\"[Feature #13884](https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/13884) added some improvements to `and`, `or` and `diff` operations, and also new assertions grouped on their own namespace, some of those assertions needed to be removed from `test_MINUS` since are already on `test_MINUS_big_array`:\\r\\nhttps://github.com/ruby/ruby/blob/42bb73cf64bc4a122b80eb2262f5b9c47381a024/test/ruby/test_array.rb#L260-L264\\r\\n\\r\\nhttps://github.com/ruby/ruby/blob/42bb73cf64bc4a122b80eb2262f5b9c47381a024/test/ruby/test_array.rb#L275-L279\\r\\n\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1787\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1787/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1787/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1787/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1787\",\"id\":286242031,\"number\":1787,\"title\":\"Use -Wimplicit-fallthrough\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"shyouhei\",\"id\":15377,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/15377?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shyouhei\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/shyouhei\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shyouhei/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shyouhei/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shyouhei/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shyouhei/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shyouhei/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shyouhei/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shyouhei/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shyouhei/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shyouhei/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2018-01-05T09:58:14Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2018-02-23T03:07:43Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"author_association\":\"OWNER\",\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/pulls/1787\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1787\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1787.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1787.patch\"},\"body\":\"â€¦ unless GCC is broken. \\r\\n\\r\\nI'll merge this once https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=83696 is fixed.\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1786\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1786/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1786/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1786/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1786\",\"id\":285843278,\"number\":1786,\"title\":\"Improve Prime:prime? algorithm up to 4 times faster\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"Mycroft1891\",\"id\":11302907,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/11302907?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Mycroft1891\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/Mycroft1891\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Mycroft1891/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Mycroft1891/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Mycroft1891/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Mycroft1891/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Mycroft1891/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Mycroft1891/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Mycroft1891/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Mycroft1891/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Mycroft1891/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":9,\"created_at\":\"2018-01-03T23:46:51Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2018-02-23T03:07:43Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/pulls/1786\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1786\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1786.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1786.patch\"},\"body\":\"**Add a faster Prime:prime? algorithm**\\r\\nI worked the other day on a problem from the Euler Project and found myself using Prime:prime? to iterate over a large set of numbers. While doing that I noticed that the Prime:prime? method was a little slow. I swapped it with another algorithm I found on [SO](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1801391/what-is-the-best-algorithm-for-checking-if-a-number-is-prime). The result was incredible:\\r\\n```bash\\r\\n$ (Prime:prime?) Time to complete (10 million): 205.742023\\r\\n$ (Prime:prime?) 664579 prime numbers found\\r\\n\\r\\n$ (new_prime?) Time to complete (10 million): 50.634685\\r\\n$ (new_prime?) 664579 prime numbers found\\r\\n```\\r\\nAs you can see iterating over 10 million numbers, the new algorithm is able to find the same prime numbers 4 times faster. I ran the tests locally and everything seems to work fine.\\r\\nCould you double check ?\\r\\n  \"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1780\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1780/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1780/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1780/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1780\",\"id\":284321901,\"number\":1780,\"title\":\"Introduce RUBY_PATCHNAME constant\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"shayonj\",\"id\":1100970,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/1100970?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shayonj\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/shayonj\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shayonj/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shayonj/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shayonj/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shayonj/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shayonj/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shayonj/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shayonj/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shayonj/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/shayonj/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2017-12-23T19:10:33Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2018-02-23T03:07:42Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/pulls/1780\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1780\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1780.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1780.patch\"},\"body\":\"`RUBY_PATCHNAME` will return:\\r\\n\\r\\n- p{level}\\r\\n- dev\\r\\n- rc/preview labels\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is especially helpful when ruby is in\\r\\nrc/preview and `RUBY_PATCHLEVEL` is set to `-1`.\\r\\n\\r\\n`RUBY_PATCHNAME` is only a proposal name for the constant :)\\r\\nFeature request at https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/14217\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1769\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1769/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1769/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1769/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1769\",\"id\":279868971,\"number\":1769,\"title\":\"Make Matrix#[]= public method\",\"user\":{