ceived_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"assignees\":[{\"login\":\"marcandre\",\"id\":33770,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/33770?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/marcandre\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/marcandre\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false}],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":42,\"created_at\":\"2017-12-06T19:02:04Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2018-02-23T03:07:42Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/pulls/1769\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1769\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1769.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1769.patch\"},\"body\":\"To address this issue [#14151](https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/14151)\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1767\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1767/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1767/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1767/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1767\",\"id\":278520265,\"number\":1767,\"title\":\"gc.h: Add SET_MACHINE_STACK_END specific for Powerpc64\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"leitao\",\"id\":148379,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/148379?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/leitao\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/leitao\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/leitao/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/leitao/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/leitao/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/leitao/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/leitao/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/leitao/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/leitao/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/leitao/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/leitao/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2017-12-01T16:25:43Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2018-02-23T03:07:42Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/pulls/1767\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1767\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1767.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1767.patch\"},\"body\":\"Currently we are not able to grab the correct end/top of the stack on\\r\\npowerpc64 due to the fact that it uses the fallback function.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe fallback function does not return the correct top of the stack\\r\\nbecause it adds a new frame and the returned top of the stack contains\\r\\nthis frame overhead that could be something around 112 bytes on\\r\\nPowerpc64.\\r\\n\\r\\nThis patch simply gets the correct top of the stack pointer, which is\\r\\nalways on r1 register according to both ABI v1 and ABI v2 (Little\\r\\nendian).\\r\\n\\r\\nSigned-off-by: Breno Leitao <leitao@debian.org>\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1763\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1763/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1763/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1763/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1763\",\"id\":275415267,\"number\":1763,\"title\":\"Rename test classes to allow stable test count when running test-all -j\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"MSP-Greg\",\"id\":15081176,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/15081176?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MSP-Greg\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/MSP-Greg\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MSP-Greg/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MSP-Greg/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MSP-Greg/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MSP-Greg/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MSP-Greg/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MSP-Greg/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MSP-Greg/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MSP-Greg/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MSP-Greg/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2017-11-20T16:25:17Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2018-01-18T15:27:14Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/pulls/1763\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1763\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1763.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1763.patch\"},\"body\":\"test-all reports widely varying test counts from build to build. This seems to be due to duplicate class names in the test suite.  This stabilizes the count.  See [Ruby Issue 14121](https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/14121)\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1759\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1759/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1759/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1759/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1759\",\"id\":274679826,\"number\":1759,\"title\":\"Add #empty? to Tempfile, StringIO, File::Stat\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"mikegee\",\"id\":14068,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/14068?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mikegee\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/mikegee\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mikegee/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mikegee/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mikegee/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mikegee/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mikegee/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mikegee/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mikegee/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mikegee/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mikegee/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2017-11-16T22:03:28Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2018-02-23T03:07:41Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/pulls/1759\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1759\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1759.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1759.patch\"},\"body\":\"Rubocop prefers `empty?` over `length == 0` and `size == 0`, which is great for String, Array, Hash, etc. It would be nice if more classes implemented `#empty?` for consistency.\\r\\n\\r\\nSee related discussion at https://github.com/bbatsov/rubocop/issues/2841\\r\\n\\r\\nhttps://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/14136\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1758\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1758/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1758/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1758/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1758\",\"id\":274466061,\"number\":1758,\"title\":\" Add difference method to Array\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"Ana06\",\"id\":16052290,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/16052290?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/Ana06\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2017-11-16T10:29:34Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2018-02-23T03:07:41Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/pulls/1758\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1758\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1758.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1758.patch\"},\"body\":\"I introduce a `difference` method equivalent to the `-` operator, but which accept more than array as argument. This improved readability, and it is also coherent with the `+` operator, which has a similar `concat` method. The method doesn't modify the original object and return a new object instead. I plan to introduce a `difference!` method as well. ðŸ˜„ \\r\\n\\r\\nTests and documentation are included. :bowtie: I also corrected a small mistake in the `Array#-` documentation and link the new method from there. \\r\\n\\r\\nIt solves partially https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/14097\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1754\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1754/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1754/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1754/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1754\",\"id\":274050632,\"number\":1754,\"title\":\"FileUtils : Use Dir.children instead of Dir.entries\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"esparta\",\"id\":1037088,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/1037088?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/esparta\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/esparta/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2017-11-15T06:41:07Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2018-02-23T03:07:41Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/pulls/1754\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1754\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1754.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1754.patch\"},\"body\":\"Feature [#14109](https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/14109)\\r\\n\\r\\nDir.children is available since Feature [#11302](https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/11302).\\r\\nFileUtils uses Dir.each on an internal method encapsulated on a private class `Entry_#entry`, having no '.' neither '..' entries would make now superfluous a chained reject filtering.\\r\\n\\r\\nThis change can improve the performance of these `FileUtils` methods when the provided path covers thousands of files or directories:\\r\\n\\r\\n- chmod_R\\r\\n- chown_R\\r\\n- remove_entry\\r\\n- remove_entry_secure\\r\\n- rm_r\\r\\n- remove_dir\\r\\n- copy_entry\\r\\n\\r\\nRelated: Feature #[13896](https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/13896) \"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1753\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1753/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1753/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1753/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1753\",\"id\":273792147,\"number\":1753,\"title\":\"Set#^ is XOR\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"Ana06\",\"id\":16052290,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/16052290?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/Ana06\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2017-11-14T13:28:09Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2018-02-23T03:07:40Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/pulls/1753\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1753\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1753.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1753.patch\"},\"body\":\"The `^` operator in `Set` is commonly known as _ exclusive or_ and _XOR_ in mathematics, hardware and other programming languages. Adding _xor_ as an alias makes it much more readable and explicit and that is what we love of Ruby. â¤