tch\"},\"body\":\"The adverb usually refers to what typically or normally happens and because of that it should be used in present tense and not in future. :bowtie: \\r\\n\\r\\nReference:\\r\\nhttps://dictionary.cambridge.org/es/gramatica/gramatica-britanica/usually\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1749\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1749/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1749/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1749/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1749\",\"id\":273368365,\"number\":1749,\"title\":\"change call CGI methods from :: to .\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"artofhuman\",\"id\":1192122,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/1192122?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/artofhuman\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/artofhuman\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/artofhuman/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/artofhuman/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/artofhuman/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/artofhuman/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/artofhuman/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/artofhuman/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/artofhuman/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/artofhuman/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/artofhuman/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2017-11-13T09:52:58Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2018-02-23T03:07:40Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/pulls/1749\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1749\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1749.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1749.patch\"},\"body\":\"Hi.\\r\\nI think `::` for call methods may cause confusion. In this pr `::` call notation changed to `.` dot call. \\r\\nMaybe it makes sense only for documentation.\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1748\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1748/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1748/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1748/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1748\",\"id\":273322298,\"number\":1748,\"title\":\"URI::Generic: Respect no_proxy for both parent domain and subdomains\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"harsimranmaan\",\"id\":1289830,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/1289830?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/harsimranmaan\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/harsimranmaan\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/harsimranmaan/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/harsimranmaan/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/harsimranmaan/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/harsimranmaan/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/harsimranmaan/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/harsimranmaan/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/harsimranmaan/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/harsimranmaan/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/harsimranmaan/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":5,\"created_at\":\"2017-11-13T06:23:46Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2018-02-23T03:07:40Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/pulls/1748\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1748\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1748.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1748.patch\"},\"body\":\"It is now possible to add just the subdomains for proxy bypass.\\r\\nIn a setting where the main domain needs to go through proxy while\\r\\nthe subdomains don't, it is now possible to just add the subdomains\\r\\nto the no_proxy list.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe assumption that both subdomains and the parent domain should\\r\\nbehave the same wrt no_proxy has been removed.\\r\\n\\r\\neg: Adding .example.com in no_proxy would allow example.com\\r\\nto go through the proxy.\\r\\n\\r\\n Addresses: https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/14345\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1747\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1747/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1747/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1747/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1747\",\"id\":272929976,\"number\":1747,\"title\":\"Add union method to Array\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"Ana06\",\"id\":16052290,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/16052290?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/Ana06\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Ana06/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":5,\"created_at\":\"2017-11-10T13:19:38Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2018-02-23T03:07:40Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/pulls/1747\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1747\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1747.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/1747.patch\"},\"body\":\"I introduce a `union` method equivalent to the `|` operator, but which accept more than one array as argument. This improved readability, and it is also coherent with the `+` operator, which has a similar `concat` method. The method doesn't modify the original object and return a new object instead. :smile: I plan to send a PR for the `union!` method as well. :wink: \\r\\n\\r\\nTests are included, although there is no documentation (or I didn't find it) about how Ruby is tested, so I am not sure if I need to test this somewhere else or/and in any other way.\\r\\n\\r\\nI also didn't find any documentation regarding how the changelog is created, how the project is documented and the style that the code follows. Is there any documentation? Should I modify something? :thinking: \\r\\n\\r\\nThis solves partially https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/14097\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby/issues/1732\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby/ruby\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/